Хоп, тушунарли 🙌. Сенинг вазифанг иккита қисмга бўлинади:

  1. Саволларга назарий жавоблар → Мен сўз билан DOC файл қилиб берамиз.

  2. Амалиёт (Power Query) → Буни Power BI Desktopда .pbix файл қилиб тайёрлаб берсам, сен очиб кўрасан.

✅ 1-қисм (DOC форматда назарий жавоблар):

  • Applied Steps: Бу ерда сен қилган ҳар бир трансформация қадамлар тарзда сақланади.

  • Remove duplicates: Home → Remove Rows → Remove Duplicates.

  • Filter icon: Ушбу тугма орқали маълумотларни шарт бўйича фильтрлайсан.

  • Rename column: Устун номини иккита марта босиб “CustID” ни “CustomerID”га ўзгартириш мумкин.

  • Close & Apply: Трансформациялар сақланади ва Power BIга юкланади.

  • Remove rows Quantity < 2: Filterда Quantity устунидан “>=2” қолдирасан.

  • Split OrderDate: Transform → Split Column → By Delimiter (йил, ой, кун).

  • Replace Values: Product устунида “Mouse” ни “Computer Mouse” билан алмаштирасан.

  • Sort OrderDate (newest first): OrderDate устуни → Sort Descending.

  • Handle nulls in Price: Replace Values (null → 0) ёки Filter out nulls.

  • Custom column TotalSpent: = [Quantity] * [Price].

  • Group by CustID: Home → Group By → CustID → Sum of TotalSpent.

  • Fix date formats: Change Type → Date → Uniform format.

  • Conditional column: If Price > 100 → “High Value”, Else → “Normal”.

  • Optimize query: Ортиқча устунларни бошиданоқ Remove Columns қилиш керак.

✅ 2-қисм (Power BI Desktop .pbix файл):
Мен сен ташлаган жадваллар (Orders ва Customer_orders) билан Power Query ичида:

  • Quantity < 2 бўлган қаторларни ўчириб,

  • OrderDateдан Year, Month, Day қўшиб,

  • Mouse → Computer Mouse қилиб,

  • TotalSpent колонкаси яратиб,

  • CustID бўйича Group By қилиб,

  • Conditional колонка (High Value) қўшиб,

  • Ахирда оптимизация қилиб, тайёр .pbix файл чиқариб бераман.

from docx import Document

# Create a new Word document
doc = Document()
doc.add_heading("Lesson 3 - Data Transformation with Power Query (Part 1)", level=1)

# Add content
qa_pairs = [
    ("What is the purpose of the 'Applied Steps' pane in Power Query?",
     "The 'Applied Steps' pane records each transformation applied to the data. It allows users to track, edit, or remove steps in the data transformation process."),
    
    ("How do you remove duplicate rows in Power Query?",
     "Go to Home → Remove Rows → Remove Duplicates."),
    
    ("What does the 'Filter' icon do in Power Query?",
     "The Filter icon allows you to filter rows in a column based on values or conditions."),
    
    ("How would you rename a column from 'CustID' to 'CustomerID'?",
     "Double-click the column name and type 'CustomerID', or right-click and select 'Rename'."),
    
    ("What happens if you click 'Close & Apply' in Power Query?",
     "All transformations are saved and applied, and the data is loaded back into Power BI."),
    
    ("Remove all rows where Quantity is less than 2.",
     "Apply a filter on the Quantity column to keep only rows where Quantity >= 2."),
    
    ("Split the OrderDate column into separate 'Year,' 'Month,' and 'Day' columns.",
     "Select OrderDate → Transform → Split Column → By Delimiter or use Date → Year/Month/Day options."),
    
    ("Replace all 'Mouse' entries in the Product column with 'Computer Mouse.'",
     "Select the Product column → Right-click → Replace Values → Replace 'Mouse' with 'Computer Mouse'."),
    
    ("Sort the table by OrderDate (newest first).",
     "Select the OrderDate column → Sort Descending."),
    
    ("How would you handle null values in the Price column?",
     "Options: Replace null with 0, filter out null values, or fill values depending on the context."),
    
    ("Write custom M-code to add a column calculating TotalSpent = Quantity * Price.",
     "Add Column → Custom Column with formula: [Quantity] * [Price]."),
    
    ("Group the table by CustID to show total spending per customer.",
     "Go to Home → Group By → Group by CustID → Aggregate TotalSpent (Sum)."),
    
    ("Fix inconsistent date formats (e.g., 01/10/2023 vs. 2023-01-10) in OrderDate.",
     "Change Data Type of OrderDate column to Date, ensuring consistent format."),
    
    ("Create a conditional column: Label orders as 'High Value' if Price > 100.",
     "Go to Add Column → Conditional Column → If [Price] > 100 then 'High Value' else 'Normal'."),
    
    ("Optimize the query to reduce refresh time (e.g., remove unused columns early).",
     "Remove unnecessary columns at the start of the transformation process to optimize performance.")
]

for q, a in qa_pairs:
    doc.add_heading(q, level=2)
    doc.add_paragraph(a)

# Save document
file_path = "/mnt/data/Lesson3_PowerQuery.docx"

python
import pandas as pd

# Create Orders dataframe
orders_data = {
    "CustID": [101, 102, 101, 103],
    "Name": ["Alice", "Bob", "Alice", "Charlie"],
    "OrderDate": ["2023-01-10", "2023-01-15", "2023-01-20", "2023-01-25"],
    "Product": ["Laptop", "Mouse", "Keyboard", "Monitor"],
    "Quantity": [1, 3, 2, 1],
    "Price": [1200, 25, 80, 300]
}
orders_df = pd.DataFrame(orders_data)

# Create Customer_orders dataframe
customers_data = {
    "CustID": [101, 102, 103],
    "Name": ["Alice", "Bob", "Charlie"],
    "Email": ["alice@example.com", "bob@example.com", "charlie@example.com"]
}
customers_df = pd.DataFrame(customers_data)

# Save to Excel file with two sheets
excel_path = "/mnt/data/PowerQuery_Lesson3_Data.xlsx"
with pd.ExcelWriter(excel_path, engine="openpyxl") as writer:
    orders_df.to_excel(writer, sheet_name="Orders", index=False)
    customers_df.to_excel(writer, sheet_name="Customer_orders", index=False)

excel_path

Бу кодни қуйидаги қадамлар орқали ишлатасан:

🔹 M-код (Power Query):

m
let
    // Orders jadvalini yuklash
    Source = Excel.Workbook(File.Contents("C:\Users\YourPath\PowerQuery_Lesson3_Data.xlsx"), null, true),
    Orders_Sheet = Source{[Name="Orders"]}[Content],
    #"Changed Type" = Table.TransformColumnTypes(Orders_Sheet,
        {{"CustID", Int64.Type}, {"Name", type text}, {"OrderDate", type date},
         {"Product", type text}, {"Quantity", Int64.Type}, {"Price", type number}}),

    // Quantity < 2 bo'lganlarni olib tashlash
    #"Filtered Rows" = Table.SelectRows(#"Changed Type", each [Quantity] >= 2),

    // OrderDate ni Year, Month, Day ga ajratish
    #"Inserted Year" = Table.AddColumn(#"Filtered Rows", "Year", each Date.Year([OrderDate]), Int64.Type),
    #"Inserted Month" = Table.AddColumn(#"Inserted Year", "Month", each Date.Month([OrderDate]), Int64.Type),
    #"Inserted Day" = Table.AddColumn(#"Inserted Month", "Day", each Date.Day([OrderDate]), Int64.Type),

    // Product ustunida Mouse -> Computer Mouse qilib almashtirish
    #"Replaced Value" = Table.ReplaceValue(#"Inserted Day","Mouse","Computer Mouse",Replacer.ReplaceText,{"Product"}),

    // Null qiymatlarni Price ustunida 0 bilan almashtirish
    #"Replaced Nulls" = Table.ReplaceValue(#"Replaced Value",null,0,Replacer.ReplaceValue,{"Price"}),

    // Yangi TotalSpent ustuni
    #"Added Custom" = Table.AddColumn(#"Replaced Nulls", "TotalSpent", each [Quantity] * [Price], type number),

    // High Value shartli ustuni
    #"Added Conditional" = Table.AddColumn(#"Added Custom", "ValueLabel",
        each if [Price] > 100 then "High Value" else "Normal", type text),

    // Keraksiz ustunlarni olib tashlab optimizatsiya qilish
    #"Removed Other Columns" = Table.SelectColumns(#"Added Conditional",
        {"CustID","Name","OrderDate","Product","Quantity","Price","Year","Month","Day","TotalSpent","ValueLabel"}),

    // Sort OrderDate bo'yicha (newest first)
    #"Sorted Rows" = Table.Sort(#"Removed Other Columns",{{"OrderDate", Order.Descending}}),

    // Customer_orders jadvalini yuklash
    Customers_Sheet = Source{[Name="Customer_orders"]}[Content],
    #"Changed Type1" = Table.TransformColumnTypes(Customers_Sheet,
        {{"CustID", Int64.Type}, {"Name", type text}, {"Email", type text}}),

    // Orders va Customer_ordersni CustID orqali qo'shish
    #"Merged Queries" = Table.NestedJoin(#"Sorted Rows", {"CustID"}, #"Changed Type1", {"CustID"}, "Customer_orders", JoinKind.LeftOuter),
    #"Expanded Customer_orders" = Table.ExpandTableColumn(#"Merged Queries", "Customer_orders", {"Email"}, {"Email"}),

    // CustID bo'yicha grouping (total spending per customer)
    #"Grouped Rows" = Table.Group(#"Expanded Customer_orders", {"CustID", "Name", "Email"},
        {{"Total Spent", each List.Sum([TotalSpent]), type number}})
in
    #"Grouped Rows"

Lesson 2 – Importing Data into Power BI

1. Power BI qanday ma’lumot manbalariga ulangan bo‘la oladi?
   - Excel fayllari
   - SQL Server ma’lumotlar bazasi
   - CSV, JSON, XML va boshqalar

2. Power BI Desktopga ma’lumot import qilishdagi birinchi qadam nima?
   - Home menyusidan “Get Data” tugmasini bosish.

3. Import qilingan ma’lumotlarni yangilash uchun nima qilinadi?
   - Home menyusidan “Refresh” tugmasi bosiladi.

4. Power BI to‘g‘ridan-to‘g‘ri qaysi fayl formatlarni import qila oladi? (2 ta)
   - Excel (.xlsx)
   - CSV (.csv)

5. Data source tanlangandan keyin “Navigator” oynasi nima ko‘rsatadi?
   - Tanlangan fayldagi barcha sheets yoki jadval nomlarini.

⚡ Power BI Desktopda bajariladigan TASKLAR

Task 1: Faylni yuklash

  • Sales_Data.csv faylini import qil.

  • Faqatgina Product va Price ustunlarini tanlab load qil.

Task 2: Ma’lumotlarni tozalash

  • OrderDate ustunini Year, Month, Day ga ajrat.

Task 3: Hisoblash

  • TotalSpent = Quantity * Price formula asosida yangi ustun qo‘sh.

  • ValueLabel qo‘sh → agar TotalSpent > 100 bo‘lsa "High", aks holda "Normal".

Task 4: Jadval qo‘shish

  • Customer_orders jadvalini ham import qil.

  • Uni Orders jadvali bilan CustID orqali bog‘la. (One-to-Many).

Task 5: Vizualizatsiyalar

  1. Pie Chart → Product bo‘yicha Quantity.

  2. Bar Chart → Year/Month bo‘yicha TotalSpent.

Zo‘r 👌 endi Lesson 4ni ham ikkiga ajratib chiqaman:

📄 Lesson4_answers.txt (og‘zaki javoblar)

  1. Merge va Append farqi

    • Merge – ikki jadvalni birlashtiradi (qo‘shma ustun asosida).

    • Append – ustunlari bir xil bo‘lgan jadvallarni bir-birining ostiga qo‘shadi.

  2. Full Name ustunini bo‘lish

    • Transform → Split Column → By Delimiter (bo‘sh joy “Space” bo‘yicha).

  3. Pivot Columns

    • Ustundagi qiymatlarni yangi ustunlarga aylantirish uchun ishlatiladi. Masalan, “Product”ni pivot qilib, “Quantity”ni yig‘indisi sifatida olish.

  4. Undo Step

    • Applied Steps panelida keraksiz qadamni o‘chirish yoki “Ctrl+Z” ishlatish.

  5. Reference va Duplicate farqi

    • Duplicate – butunlay nusxa (mustaqil query).

    • Reference – bog‘langan nusxa (asosiy querydagi o‘zgarishlarga ta’sir qiladi).

  6. Fill Down

    • Bo‘sh (null) kataklarni yuqoridagi qiymat bilan to‘ldirish.

  7. Extract Domain from Email

    • Transform → Extract → Text After Delimiter → “@” belgisi.

  8. try…otherwise

    • Xatolik bo‘lsa, muqobil qiymat qo‘yish. Masalan:

      m
      try [A] / [B] otherwise 0

  9. Function to clean phone numbers

    • M function yoziladi → Text.Remove([Phone], {"-"," "}).

  10. Optimallashtirish

    • Ortiqcha bosqichlarni o‘chirish, bir nechta Transform’ni bitta bosqichda bajarish, kerakmas ustunlarni erta olib tashlash.

🖥 Power BI Tasklar (Lesson 4 amaliy)

  1. Orders.csv va Customers.xlsx fayllarini yukla.

  2. Ularni CustID bo‘yicha Merge (Inner Join) qil.

  4. Ikki jadvalni Append qil (masalan, Orders_Jan.csv + Orders_Feb.csv).

  5. Email ustunida bo‘sh qiymatlar bo‘lsa, Fill Down qil.

  6. Email ustunidan domain qismini ajratib ol.

  7. Sales ustunida xatolik (masalan, 0 ga bo‘lish) yuz bersa, try…otherwise bilan hal qil.

  8. Jan_Sales, Feb_Sales kabi ustunlarni Unpivot qilib, Month va Sales ustunlari hosil qil.

  9. Telefon raqamlarini tozalovchi function yarat.

  10. 10+ qadamli query bo‘lsa, optimallashtirib bosqichlarni kamaytir.
